PATCH: Change visibility conditions for event action buttons
Visibility conditions for 'update', 'cancel', 'undo' and 'finish' buttons in EventsEditScreen.php have been updated. This ensures that the buttons are only shown when the event status is either 'INCOMING' or 'STARTED', providing a more intuitive user interface.

PATCH: Fix visibility conditions for event buttons in EventsEditScreen
Update the visibility conditions for the event action buttons
Conditions for displaying the 'update', 'cancel', 'undo' and 'finish' event buttons in EventsEditScreen.php have been modified. This update enhances event state checks for showing or hiding buttons, making the usability more intuitive. The visibility now depends on the existence of events, followed by the status of these events.

PATCH: Update event visibility conditions in EventsEditScreen
Modify the conditions to show event buttons
The conditions to show or hide the 'update', 'cancel', 'undo', and 'finish' event buttons have been changed in EventsEditScreen.php. Previously, visibility depended on both the existence of the events and their status. Now, event existence is checked first and then their status, optimizing the visibility conditions.

PATCH: Remove admin role check from UserEditScreen
save method
This update removes the check for admin role in the save function of UserEditScreen.php. This was resulting in an info message and redirect if a user was an admin. This particular validation and redirection logic was not needed here, hence removed.

PATCH: Refactor UserUpdated event to use new presenter
Updated the UserUpdated event to use the UserPresenters class from the App\Orchid namespace instead of the UserPresenter class from the App\Platform namespace. This change enabled more granular control over the user update process and streamlined codebase by eliminating duplication of similar classes in different namespaces.
